messages.message: Is there anyone that can help find a workaround for this for tomorrow’s BAML training? Aaron and I have been trying everything to get it to work
Don’t want to volunteer the wrong person, but maybe @Jonathan Shih who was working in classifier land a short while ago might know? Looks like a path building bug.
Thankfully @Jonathan Shih is here with me and will check it out when we get to the hotel!! Currently all of his devices are very out of power
that’s what happens when you try to upload 3GB of data on a plane.
LOL finally got power on my laptop. going out to dinner soon, but will investigate more when we get back.
btw @Aaron Vontell is this happening on master?
i just ran a custom classifier and it ran fine… will investigate more later https://instabase.com/apps/flow/ib_eng/tests/fs/Test%20Drive/files/workspace-ted/classifier-test/Workflows/#
@Aaron Vontell figured out the issue. the custom script was not expecting both ibocr and text to be set, and it was built for the old ibocr format. no need for any backend changes
